**Generating Flavor Text**

I'm currently focused on how to best integrate AI-generated flavor text into the `index.tsx` file for the board game. The main task is updating the `generatePropertyImage` function to also produce a short, evocative description for boats. I'm exploring the best way to handle this, whether it involves extending the existing function or implementing a new, more modular mechanism for generating both images and text.


**Refining Asset Generation**

I'm now integrating text generation within the existing asset generation process in `index.tsx`. The goal is to produce Icelandic descriptions alongside images for properties and restaurant spaces. The `BoardSpace` interface already has a `description` field, which I'll populate. I'll rename `generatePropertyImage` to `generatePropertyAssets`, or integrate the text generation call directly to keep things simple. My prompt will request a short, evocative Icelandic flavor description.


**Updating Asset Generation**

I'm now focusing on integrating text generation directly into the asset pipeline. I plan to enhance the `generatePropertyAssets` function to generate Icelandic descriptions using `gemini-3-flash-preview` alongside images. The `SpaceCard` component will be updated to display this description, potentially with an "i" icon to reveal the text in a tooltip or overlay. I'm keen on how this streamlined approach will affect the `handleLandOnSpace` function.


**Expanding Asset Generation**

I've confirmed that the `isGenerated` flag handles both image and description generation, so I'll keep it as is for now. My next step is to update the existing `generatePropertyImage` function to also produce Icelandic descriptions using `gemini-3-flash-preview`. The function will update the state with both the image URL and the new description.


**Implementing UI Interaction**

I'm now integrating the generated text into the `SpaceCard` component. I've decided to add an "Info" button (using the `lucide-react` `Info` icon) to toggle the display of a description overlay on click. The overlay will contain the Icelandic flavor text. To accomplish this, I'm adding a `showInfo` state to `SpaceCard`. I am considering how this will be presented in the UI, and believe that an absolute overlay is the most promising approach. I'll modify `index.tsx` to handle this new UI element.


**Refining Concurrent Generation**

I'm now focusing on optimizing concurrent generation of assets. I'm leveraging `Promise.all` to fetch both image and text concurrently. I'm crafting a Gemini prompt to generate a stylized image with an Icelandic harbor setting, and another for a short Icelandic description. The image prompt specifies a particular style, mood, and color palette. The text prompt requests a short, fun Icelandic description.


**Integrating Asset Display**

I've integrated the generation logic into the UI. I've updated the `generatePropertyAssets` function to correctly handle the asynchronous nature of fetching both image and text. I've successfully implemented the "Info" button within the `SpaceCard` component, which toggles the visibility of the Icelandic description overlay. I'm satisfied with the integration and will proceed to test the user interface.


**Refining Button Integration**

I'm now refining the integration of the "Info" button and description overlay within the `SpaceCard` component. I've corrected an import statement for the `Info` icon and ensured that the overlay closes on click. I need to make some small tweaks.


**Verifying Model Integration**

I've verified that `gemini-2.5-flash-image` and `gemini-3-flash-preview` are correctly specified for image and text generation, respectively, within the `generatePropertyAssets` function. My prompts will request Icelandic text, with a maximum of 15 words and an atmospheric style, while image prompts now specify a particular style, mood, and color palette. The `BoardSpace` interface and `SpaceCard` component definitions are also confirmed to be correct.


**Refactoring Image Generation**

I'm now focusing on updating the existing `generatePropertyImage` function to handle both image and Icelandic description generation. I will ensure the AI generates and populates the `description` field of the `BoardSpace` interface, even for existing board spaces. I will overwrite the existing English descriptions. Then, I'll add an "info" button to the `SpaceCard` component.


**Streamlining Asset Creation**

I'm now streamlining asset creation. I'm focusing on making the generation of both images and text fully concurrent. Specifically, I'm refactoring the `generatePropertyAssets` function. I'm leveraging `Promise.all` to fetch both image and Icelandic description, using separate prompts optimized for each model and task. I am working on the exact prompts.


**Implementing Asset Handling**

I've refactored the `generatePropertyAssets` function to correctly update the `BoardSpace` state with both image URLs and Icelandic descriptions, even when assets are already generated. I'm focusing on handling image and text generation within the same try/catch block for error management, and am now incorporating error logging to provide better feedback. I have verified that the image and text are being applied to the space, and that the UI can handle the update.



**Refining Overlay Integration**

I'm now refining the description overlay within the `SpaceCard` component. I'm focusing on ensuring it's displayed correctly and provides a seamless user experience. I've adjusted styling and positioning to ensure the overlay remains visible but unobtrusive. My next step involves testing different scenarios.


**Optimizing Overlay Interactions**

I'm now focused on optimizing the interaction behavior of the information overlay, ensuring a better user experience. I've successfully implemented click-to-close functionality, but I'm refining the positioning to maintain the current visual hierarchy. I'm also considering additional visual cues to make the interaction more intuitive.


**Enhancing Icon Display**

I'm now integrating icons into the `SpaceCard` to indicate special space types. I'm focusing on incorporating icons for spaces like "CHANCE," "START," "JAIL," and "STORM." I'm also ensuring the existing visual hierarchy and information presentation are maintained. I'm looking at adjusting the size to match the design.


**Integrating Icon Additions**

I'm now integrating icons into the UI, specifically for special space types. I've updated the import statement to include the `Info` icon from `lucide-react`. I will ensure that the existing functionality, particularly the description overlay integration, remains unchanged after this modification. I will focus on integrating these icons into the `SpaceCard` component, and am ensuring the correct visual styling.



**Refining Asset Imports**

I'm now refining the import statements to streamline the code. I've removed icons I am not using, and verified the structure for `BoardSpace`. I'll proceed with replacing the existing image generation and UI components with the new logic, ensuring the `description` field is populated correctly.


**Refining Visual Integration**

I'm now refining the integration of AI-generated visuals. I'm focusing on ensuring the visual generation process for properties is robust and efficient. I have updated the `generatePropertyImage` function to leverage `gemini-2.5-flash-image`, as the existing logic does not work as expected. I will improve prompt to produce a stylized, moody, oil-painting image of the location in an Icelandic harbor setting, with a rustic color palette.


